snippet: The return of Zhou Fengsuo, who helped lead the 1989 protests, came despite China’s intensified security measures on the anniversary of the crackdown.
abstract: Zhou Fengsuo, former protest organizer who is on Chinese government's 1989 list of 21 most-wanted students, reports that he was able to slip back into China undetected, despite intensified security measures on anniversary of Tiananmen Square crackdown; he spent two days visiting friends in a police detention center before being caught and put on flight back to United States, where he has lived for two decades and has citizenship.
lead_paragraph: The return of Zhou Fengsuo, who helped lead the 1989 protests, came despite China’s intensified security measures on the anniversary of the crackdown.
